<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870626-0112 </DOCNO><HL> Leaseway TransportationIs Acquired by Investors</HL><DD> 06/26/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> CCITENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)TRANSPORTATION, TRUCK AND SHIP LINES, RAILROADS (TRA) </IN><DATELINE> CLEVELAND  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Leaseway Transportation Corp. said an investor group led by CitiCorp Capital Investors Ltd. completed its leveraged buyout of the trucking company.    As previously reported, the CitiCorp group agreed to pay $51 a share to acquire the outstanding shares of Leaseway in a transaction valued at $600 million. Gerald M. McDonough, Leaseway's chairman and chief executive officer, said proceeds of the financing for the leveraged buyout are in place and all other requirements and conditions of the agreement have been fulfilled.    In composite trading on the New York Stock Exchange, Leaseway closed yesterday at $50.875 a share, up 12.5 cents. </TEXT></DOC>